VGUDIPOODI SRIHARIYoga Vandana of Bangalore presented a veena recital at a concert jointly organised by Nada Sudha and Sahithi Sravanthi. A disciple of Guru Subhashini Sastri and Guru V.S. Ananta Rao, a former senior staff artiste of Hyderabad AIR, Yoga Vandana herself is an A-grade veena player of AIR and Doordarshan.Yoga Vandana is the daughter of Prof. Veturi Anandamurthy, renowned researcher and  the son of another great  -   Veturi Prabhakara Sastry. Vandana has presented numerous concerts in prestigious forums thereby gaining good experience. She is a diploma holder with honours in veena and has also passed the Alankar Exam, conducted by Akhil Bharathiya Gandharva Maha Vidyalaya.Natakuranji varnamopened her show.Vandeham Jagadvallabhamof Annamacharya inHamsadhwaniandAmbavaaniof Muthiah Bhagavathar inKeeravaniwere the invocatory numbers.GanamurtheinGanamurthi,Jalandhara Supreethaof Deekshitar inValajiwere pleasant offerings.Sankarabharanamwas her major number. Her presentation of theraga,swarasand thekirtanawere in vocalist style.The recital was a continuous melody-filledragaessay, enjoyable at every sequence. . Thenerevalandswaraexercise was laudable.Venkatachala NilayaminSindhu Bhairaviand a Tamil song of Rajaji (Kurai Mondrum Illaiand Balamurali'stillanainDwijavanthigave a smooth finish. Srinivasa Gopalan accompanied her on mridangam.Like daughterThe other concert of the evening was a vocal concert by Yoga Kirtana, very young artiste. Daughter of Vandana, the girl is in the formative stage but displayed much promise. She has excellent voice with good range and has developed the knack of throwing her voice fully, with clearsahityaexpression. Though it was a brief recital, she displayed good talent and showed the potential to develop into a good artiste.Disciple of Vidushi P. Ramaa, an eminent vocalist of Bangalore, she has already acquired the skill of expanding a raga methodically and then presentingswara kalpanawith good discipline.Kirtana started her recital withViriboniAta Thala VarnaminBhairaviand followed it up withSri MahaganapathiminAthana.Kalyaniwas essayed carefully.Pawan Singh accompanied her on the violin and Srinivasa Gopalan was on mridangam.Bottom Template Starts
